    <etym xml:lang="ru">Ср. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>deli,
                däli</w><gloss><q>глупый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>дурак</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>сумасшедший</q></gloss></mentioned>, ; проникло и в другие
        кавказские языки: <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>delä,
                dejlä</w><gloss><q>глупый</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>дурак</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lez"
                ><lang/><w>deli</w><gloss><q>сумасшедший</q></gloss></mentioned>. Появление в начале
        %iæ%i, осмысляемого, по-видимому, как α privativum, явилось результатом восприятия этого
        слова как негативного: „не-разумный“, „без-умный“. Может быть, сыграла также роль
        контаминация с <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
            ><lang/><w>abdāl</w><gloss><q>отшельник</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>безумец</q></gloss></mentioned>, , ср. <mentioned xml:lang="av"
                ><lang/><w>’adal-</w><gloss><q>глупый</q></gloss></mentioned>. <bibl><ref
                target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>80</biblScope></bibl> выводил из
        %i*a-turya%i, ср. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
            ><lang/><w>turas</w><gloss><q>мощный</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>быстрый</q></gloss></mentioned>, . Однако значения плохо
        вяжутся.</etym>
    <etym xml:lang="en">Cf. <mentioned xml:lang="trk"><lang/><w>deli,
                däli</w><gloss><q>stupid</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>fool</q></gloss></mentioned>, <mentioned xml:lang="trk"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>crazy</q></gloss></mentioned>, ; found its way into other
        Caucasian languages: <mentioned xml:lang="kbd"><lang/><w>delä,
                dejlä</w><gloss><q>stupid</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned xml:lang="kbd"
                    ><w/><gloss><q>fool</q></gloss></mentioned>, , <mentioned xml:lang="lez"
                ><lang/><w>deli</w><gloss><q>crazy</q></gloss></mentioned>. The appearance of %iæ%i
        at the beginning, which was treated, apparently, as α privativum, was the result of the fact
        that this word was percepted as negative: “not-intelligent”, “without-intelligent”. Perhaps,
        contamination with <mentioned xml:lang="ar"
                ><lang/><w>abdāl</w><gloss><q>отшельник</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="ar"><w/><gloss><q>безумец</q></gloss></mentioned>, played its role, cf.
            <mentioned xml:lang="av"><lang/><w>’adal-</w><gloss><q>stupid</q></gloss></mentioned>.
                <bibl><ref target="#ref_Вс._Миллер._Gr."/><biblScope>80</biblScope></bibl> traced it
        back to %i*a-turya%i, cf. <mentioned xml:lang="sa"
                ><lang/><w>turas</w><gloss><q>powerful</q></gloss></mentioned><mentioned
            xml:lang="sa"><w/><gloss><q>fast</q></gloss></mentioned>, . However, the meanings do not
        fit well.</etym>
